  "text": "## OpenTelemetry Span Creation Patterns Across Monitoring Stack\n\n### Prometheus/Prometheus Patterns\n\n**Tracer Initialization:**\nPrometheus uses the global OpenTelemetry tracer provider accessed directly via `otel.Tracer(\"\")`, importing from `go.opentelemetry.io/otel` and `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace`. This is visible in:\n- `storage/remote/queue_manager.go:2298` - `otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"Remote Send Batch\")`\n- `storage/remote/client.go:402` - `otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"Remote Read\", trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient))`\n- `util/stats/query_stats.go:199` - `NewSpanTimer` function\n- `scrape/scrape.go:748` - `otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"Scrape\", trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient))`\n- `rules/group.go:515` - `otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"rule\")`\n\n**Span Start/End Calls:**\nPrometheus uses the pattern `ctx, span := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, name)` followed by `defer span.End()`. Examples:\n- `storage/remote/client.go:402-403` with Remote Read span\n- `storage/remote/queue_manager.go:2298` returning context and span\n- `scrape/scrape.go:748-749` with Scrape span\n\n**Span Attributes Setting:**\nAttributes are set using `span.SetAttributes()` with `attribute.*` type-specific functions:\n- `storage/remote/queue_manager.go:2299-2311` - Sets request_size, samples, try, remote_name, remote_url, exemplars, histograms\n- `rules/group.go:516` - `sp.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"name\", rule.Name()))`\n- `promql/engine.go:250` - `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(queryTag, q.stmt.String()))`\n- Imports `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/attribute` and optionally semantic conventions `semconv`\n\n**Span Context Access:**\nPrometheus can check if a span exists and is sampled:\n- `rules/group.go:527` - `if sp.SpanContext().IsSampled() && sp.SpanContext().HasTraceID()`\n- `promql/engine.go:249` - `if span := trace.SpanFromContext(ctx); span != nil`\n\n**Span Kind Configuration:**\nSpan kind is set at creation time using `trace.WithSpanKind()`:\n- `storage/remote/client.go:402` - `trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient)` for Remote Read\n- `scrape/scrape.go:748` - `trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient)` for Scrape\n\n### Grafana/Grafana Patterns\n\n**Tracer Initialization and Dependency Injection:**\nGrafana uses a more sophisticated initialization approach through a TracingService:\n- `pkg/infra/tracing/tracing.go:108-115` - `NewNoopTracerService()` creates noop tracer with `otel.SetTracerProvider(tp)`\n- `pkg/infra/tracing/tracing.go:130-180` - `initJaegerTracerProvider()` configures Jaeger exporter\n- `pkg/server/wire.go:215-216` - Dependency injection pattern: `func otelTracer() trace.Tracer { return otel.GetTracerProvider().Tracer(\"grafana\") }`\n- `pkg/server/wire.go:310-313` - Wire setup for tracing service and otel bindings\n\n**Tracer Retrieval:**\n- Services use `otel.GetTracerProvider().Tracer(\"service-name\")` for getting named tracers\n- `apps/iam/pkg/reconcilers/zanzana_service.go:28,61,106` - Direct tracer retrieval and span creation\n- `pkg/infra/httpclient/httpclientprovider/tracing_middleware.go:28` - Tracer passed as middleware parameter\n\n**Span Start/End with Attributes at Creation:**\nGrafana often combines span creation with attributes using `trace.WithAttributes()`:\n- `pkg/services/team/teamimpl/team.go:42-43` - `_, span := s.tracer.Start(ctx, \"team.CreateTeam\", trace.WithAttributes(attribute.Int64(\"orgID\", cmd.OrgID)))`\n- `pkg/services/playlist/playlistimpl/playlist.go:46-47` - `ctx, span := s.tracer.Start(ctx, \"playlists.Get\")` then `defer span.End()`\n- `apps/iam/pkg/reconcilers/zanzana_service.go:62-64` - `ctx, span := tracer.Start(ctx, \"ZanzanaPermissionStore.GetFolderParents\", trace.WithAttributes(...))`\n- `pkg/infra/httpclient/httpclientprovider/tracing_middleware.go:28-29` - `ctx, span := tracer.Start(req.Context(), \"HTTP Outgoing Request\", trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient))`\n\n**Span Attributes Setting After Creation:**\nMany Grafana files use `span.SetAttributes()` after span creation:\n- `pkg/tsdb/tempo/metrics_stream.go:114` - `span.SetAttributes(attribute.Int(\"message_count\", messageCount))`\n- `pkg/registry/apis/dashboard/datasources.go:41,58` - `span.SetAttributes(attribute.Int64(\"org_id\", nsInfo.OrgID))`\n- `pkg/services/accesscontrol/migrator/migrator.go:65,77,107,113-115` - Multiple attribute settings with migration tracking\n- `pkg/infra/httpclient/httpclientprovider/tracing_middleware.go:34,40-41,54,57` - HTTP-related attributes via semantic conventions\n\n**Span Error Recording and Status Setting:**\nGrafana consistently uses both error recording and status setting together:\n- `pkg/tsdb/tempo/metrics_stream.go:94-96` - `span.RecordError(err)` then `span.SetStatus(codes.Error, err.Error())`\n- `pkg/infra/httpclient/httpclientprovider/tracing_middleware.go:44-46` - Error path: `span.SetStatus(codes.Error, \"request failed\")` and `span.RecordError(err)`\n- `pkg/services/accesscontrol/migrator/migrator.go:72-73,100` - `patternSpan.RecordError(errFind)` then `patternSpan.End()`\n- `pkg/modules/tracing/listener.go:93-96` - Complete pattern: `SetStatus` with `codes.Error` or `codes.Ok`, then `RecordError` if error\n- `pkg/storage/unified/resource/access.go:128,162,207` - Error attributes: `SetAttributes(attribute.Bool(\"allowed\", false))` before status/error\n\nImports needed: `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/codes` for error status constants.\n\n**Semantic Conventions:**\nBoth projects use semantic conventions:\n- `pkg/infra/httpclient/httpclientprovider/tracing_middleware.go:13` - `semconv \"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/semconv/v1.17.0\"`\n- HTTP attributes: `semconv.HTTPURL()`, `semconv.HTTPMethod()`, `semconv.HTTPStatusCode()`, `semconv.HTTPResendCount()`\n- `storage/remote/queue_manager.go:611` - Prometheus uses semantic conventions: `semconv.HTTPResendCount(try)`\n\n**Span Nesting and Context Propagation:**\nBoth projects demonstrate nested spans:\n- `pkg/services/accesscontrol/migrator/migrator.go:63-110` - Outer span contains inner loop with pattern-specific spans\n- `pkg/registry/apis/dashboard/datasources.go` - Spans created from context passed through function calls\n- Prometheus uses span context for logging: `rules/group.go:527-528` - Extract and log trace ID\n\n### Key Differences\n\n1. **Tracer Initialization:** Prometheus uses global `otel.Tracer(\"\")` directly, while Grafana initializes through `TracingService` with dependency injection via Wire\n2. **Error Handling:** Grafana consistently pairs `RecordError()` with `SetStatus()`, while Prometheus mostly omits error handling in traced operations\n3. **Semantic Conventions:** Grafana uses more structured semantic conventions for HTTP (v1.17.0), while Prometheus uses them selectively\n4. **Span Kind:** Both use `trace.WithSpanKind()`, particularly for client operations\n5. **Attribute Timing:** Grafana uses both `trace.WithAttributes()` at creation and `SetAttributes()` post-creation, while Prometheus primarily uses post-creation `SetAttributes()`"
}

